# Quick Setup for New Service

## Step 1: Add Domain to /etc/hosts
```bash
# For local-only access
echo "127.0.0.1 yourdomain.local" | sudo tee -a /etc/hosts

# For network access (use your IP)
echo "192.168.0.18 yourdomain.local" | sudo tee -a /etc/hosts
```

## Step 2: Configure Nginx
Edit `/opt/homebrew/etc/nginx/nginx.conf` and add:

```nginx
# Your Service Name
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name yourdomain.local;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:YOUR_PORT;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
        proxy_set_header Connection 'upgrade';
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_cache_bypass $http_upgrade;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
    }
}
```

## Step 3: Reload Nginx
```bash
nginx -t && brew services reload nginx
```

## Real Example: prism.ai (Successfully Configured)
- **Service**: RichPrism AI on port 9393
- **Domain**: prism.ai
- **Result**: http://localhost:9393 → http://prism.ai

### prism.ai nginx config:
```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name prism.ai;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:9393;
        # ... proxy headers ...
    }
}
```

